SQL GROUP BY

Exercise:
List the number of customers in each country.


SELECT 
COUNT
(CustomerID),
Country
FROM Customers GROUP BY Country;  # CORRECT!


Exercise:
List the number of customers in each country, ordered by the country with the most customers first.


SELECT 
COUNT(CustomerID), Country
FROM Customers
GROUP BY Country
ORDER BY 
COUNT(CustomerID) DESC;  # CORRECT! DESC; descending; largest to smallest, 9 to 0, and/or Z to A.

